---
source: tests/contracts.rs
assertion: maintenance job commands run shared steward handlers and persist history
schema:
  run: ee.maintenance.job_run.v1
  list: ee.maintenance.job_list.v1
  show: ee.maintenance.job_show.v1
  row: ee.maintenance.job_row.v1
contracts:
  - job run accepts persisted steward job kinds and rejects unknown kinds
  - job run uses the same handler path as the steward runner
  - job run persists success, failure, cancellation, and lock-busy outcomes
  - job list reads durable history with kind and since filters
  - job show reads a full durable row by history ID or steward job ID
  - concurrent triggers for the same workspace return lock-busy without running the handler
evidence:
  - requestedJob
  - outcome
  - rowsAffected
  - jobHistoryId
  - jobId
  - historyPath
  - startedAt
  - completedAt
  - repair
